				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Yes, let's look at the math.  It has been $9.89 for 2.5 yrs.  After taking into account inflation (CPI) for the last 2.5 yrs that price should have risen to $10.40.  Now since EQ has started there have been 3 expansion. If you assume that with each expansion there was a 10% increase in product (more zones, classes, races items)(some expansion added more some less) that would raise the price up to a hefty $13.84. If you take into consideration the upcoming Planes of Power expansion (for this excercise I will assume a 5% increase in product value) you come to a total of $14.53.  <BR>
<BR>
Hmm, all things considered $12.95 doesn't sound too bad.<BR>
<BR>
P.S. I do agree Verant could improve upon many aspects and I think they should after the increase of fee.  But they must have done something right, I mean look at how many are complaining.
