				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmm, 3 more bucks a month... not too bad.  Though let's get some more things fixed in game. I am happy with the new ideas and areas... especially the Vah Shir... pretty cool race.<BR>
<BR>
Now, let's get on something someone said about your character name and Sony/Verant owning it...<BR>
Bullsh!t... If you put your name as a character, are you suddenly owned by the company?  I don't think so my friend...<BR>
...by the way, I have character names that are in my comics (coming out soon boys and girls) and they are based - slightly - off of characters I have in the game..which of course, came from old characters I used to play in D&amp;D...<BR>
<BR>
$12.99 a month is not too bad... but this extra money better be going to game use and maintainence/upgrade stuff.  I do feel for those that had to dish out cash to upgrade their computers and now have to donate more to play. All those extra RAMs and video cards tend to add up.<BR>
<BR>
My only complaint with EQ is the naming policy... sure I'm glad I don't have to put up with 100 Maximus's and Merlin names that UO had...(thank god! I hated all those DoOd names too) but I have actually met other people with the name Ryan... can you believe that?  And I had actually met someone who had my first and last name... which is rare in itself...<BR>
<BR>
...and that about enough ramblings out of me.<BR>
<BR>
Enjoy your gaming kids!
